"35:38:2" : {s: 35, a: 38, w: 2, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهَ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-laha", lb: "আল্লাহ ",e: "Allah", b: "আল্লাহকে", f: 592, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
"35:38:3" : {s: 35, a: 38, w: 3, r: "علم", t: "عَٰلِمُ", l: "عَٰلِم", lc: 18, tl: "ʿālimu", lb: "জানা, জ্ঞান লাভ করা",e: "(is the) Knower", b: "অবগত", f: 7, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
